fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">15. </div><div class="t m14b0 x6f h15 y19fe ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">From which part of our income should the Lord&apos;s </div><div class="t m27c x71 h15 y1a26 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">portion be taken? Prov. 3:9, 10. </div><div class="t me4 x48 h15 y176e ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">16. </div><div class="t mbb2 x6f h15 y63c ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What else should we render to the Lord besides </div><div class="t m560 x16 h15 y1e73 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the tithe ? Mal. 3:8. </div><div class="t me4 x48 h15 y17b7 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">17. </div><div class="t m1c90 x6f h15 y17b7 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How should we give ? </div><div class="t m5 x1b h15 y17b7 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1dfe x33 h15 y17b7 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 Cor. 9 :6, 7. </div><div class="t me4 x48 h15 y1aba ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18. </div><div class="t m1355 x6f h15 y1658 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What blessing is promised to those who return to </div><div class="t mea8 x16 h15 y1c94 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Lord His own ? Mal. 3:10-12; Prov. 11:24-26. </div><div class="t m173a x2 h2d y19bc ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Notes. </div><div class="t m988 x74 h2d y1d58 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t mf38 x60 h2d y1bff ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;I was shown that the parable of the talents has not </div><div class="t m8b8 x16 h2d y1e8a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">been fully understood. This important lesson was given to </div><div class="t m110f x16 h2d y1964 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the disciples for the benefit of Christians living in the last </div><div class="t m2c3 x16 h2d y1111 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">days. And these talents do not represent merely the ability </div><div class="t m8d6 x16 h2d y1c4d ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to preach and instruct from the Word of God. The parable </div><div class="t me75 x3e h2d y18d1 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">applies to the temporal means which God has intrusted to </div><div class="t m891 x16 h2d y1b08 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">His people. Those to whom the five and the two talents </div><div class="t m3ee x16 h2d y111a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">were given traded and doubled that which was committed </div><div class="t m58b x16 h2d y2043 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to their trust. God requires those who have possessions here </div><div class="t m2b2 x16 h2d y1be7 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to put their money out to usury for Him—to put it into the </div><div class="t m115c x16 h2d y1ba3 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cause to spread the truth. . . . I saw that some of God&apos;s </div><div class="t ma14 x16 h2d yf62 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">professed people are like the man who hid his talent in the </div><div class="t m173d x16 h2d yba9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">earth. They keep their possessions from doing good in the </div><div class="t ma79 x16 h2d y18d6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cause of </div><div class="t m1145 x49 h4a y17c5 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God.&quot;—Testimonies for the Church, Vol 1. ivtge</div><div class="t m1aeb x4d h4a y17c5 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">,</div><div class="t m77f x8a h4a y18d6 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">, 197,198 </div><div class="t m127 x74 h2d y1b3e ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t mf38 x60 h2d y1b94 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In Eden the test before man was whether he would </div><div class="t ma3e x3e h4a y2164 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nine-tenths of the women of India;never, </div><div class="t m4da x56 h4a y1d31 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> ,heard of a&apos;Saviour. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
